    "summary": "The user, a diabetic, asks for guidance on whether to skip their basal insulin due to low food intake and a current low glucose reading (75 mg/dL). The assistant provides contradictory and dangerous advice, first insisting the user must take the dose to avoid a coma, then abruptly flipping to agree that skipping the dose is the \"safest move\" despite immediately following that advice with a contradictory warning that taking the dose will cause a coma.",
